Installation
=============

- install PHP 5 sources corresponding to your PHP version
- into this current directory, run this following command :
    phpize
    ./configure --enable-jelix
    make
- then you will have a jelix.so into the subdirectory modules
- copy jelix.so into the directory which contains php extensions. Example for ubuntu 
   sudo cp modules/jelix.so /usr/lib/php5/20051025/
- modify your php.ini : add this line
    extension=jelix.so
- restart apache to activate the jelix extension.
